    <listApp>
      <app loc="1">
        <lem><g type="spiral"/></lem>
        <note>I believe a spiral may be present here, but I am not sure. PS's edition has a note anchor with the number 2 after the initial word <foreign>svasti</foreign>, but note 2 of his paper is certainly not meant to go here. I think he must have intended to re-attach note 16 here. His original note 16 is attached likewise after the opening <foreign>svasti</foreign> in the first charter edited in his article, and mentions a spiral symbol at the beginning of the line.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="1">
        <lem>-skandh<choice><sic>a</sic><corr>ā</corr></choice>vārāT</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">-skandh<choice><sic>ā</sic><corr>a</corr></choice>vārāT</rdg>
      </app>
      <app loc="2">
        <lem>lāṁc<unclear cert="low">ch</unclear>anekṣa<supplied reason="undefined">ṇa</supplied></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">lāṁccanekṣa<supplied reason="omitted">ṇa</supplied></rdg>
        <note>Since PS does not emend <foreign>cc</foreign>, I assume that this is a typo and the plate reads <foreign>cch</foreign>.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="2">
        <lem>-gotrāṇāṁ</lem>
        <note>If this is not a typo in PS, then it is unique among Eastern Cālukya plates as far as I know.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="4">
        <lem>alaṁkariṣṇor aneka-</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">alaṁkariṣṇor neka-</rdg>
      </app>
      <app loc="7">
        <lem>n<unclear cert="low">aya</unclear>-jñaḥ manur iva <unclear cert="low">vinaya</unclear>-jñaḥ</lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">nāma-jñaḥ manur iva <gap reason="undefined" quantity="3" unit="character" precision="low"/>-jñaḥ</rdg>
        <note>Compare the <ref target="DHARMA_INSVengiCalukya00006.xml">Guḍivāḍa plates (set 2) of Jayasiṁha I</ref> (line 10) and the <ref target="DHARMA_INSVengiCalukya00010.xml">Puloṁbūra grant of Jayasiṁha I</ref> (line 9).</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="9">
        <lem>putr<unclear cert="low">eṇa</unclear></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">putr<choice><sic>iṇo</sic><corr>o</corr></choice></rdg>
        <note>See the commentary for my reasoning.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="10">
        <lem>adhivasat<unclear cert="low">o</unclear></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">adhivasat</rdg>
      </app>
      <app loc="11">
        <lem source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">kanakanandyā</lem>
        <note>Either the scribe or PS's typesetter probably omitted /cāryyasya/ after this word. The number of characters in this line is approximately the same as in the neighbouring lines, so scribal omission seems more likely.</note>
      </app>
      <app loc="12">
        <lem>adhivasat<unclear cert="low">aḥ</unclear></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">adhivasat</rdg>
      </app>
      <app loc="13">
        <lem>sa<unclear cert="low">kala-rājapuru</unclear><supplied reason="omitted">ṣāN</supplied></lem>
        <rdg source="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01">saparirājapura</rdg>
      </app>
