<div type="bibliography">
  <p>Reported in <bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1990-1991"/><citedRange unit="page">20-21</citedRange><citedRange unit="appendix">A/1990-91</citedRange><citedRange unit="item">2</citedRange></bibl> with some further details at <bibl><ptr target="bib:ARIE1990-1991"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>. Edited from inked impressions by C. A. Padmanabha Sastry (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:PadmanabhaSastry1994_01"/><citedRange unit="item">B</citedRange></bibl>), without facsimiles and without translation. The present edition by Dániel Balogh is based on the published edition. However, this edition contains such an inordinate number of typographic (or other) mistakes, that duplicating it to the letter would serve no purpose, and in some cases the intent of the editors cannot be reconstructed. My edition therefore shows my conjectures of what the actual reading of the plates may be and how that should in my opinion be emended. Every locus where my "reading" of the assumed original diverges from the printed edition is marked up as unclear and tentatively in my edition, whereas loci marked as unclear by the original editors are shown here as unclear, but confidently read. My apparatus cites the printed edition where I deviate from it in a major way or where my conjecture is uncertain, but I silently correct some obvious typos, ignore some nonsensical emendations, and apply my own segmentation.</p>
